---
// src/pages/[lang]/about/index.astro
import Layout from "../../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";

// 1. OBLIGATORIO: Le decimos a Astro que genere esta página para los 3 idiomas
export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    { params: { lang: 'es' } },
    { params: { lang: 'en' } },
    { params: { lang: 'ja' } },
  ];
}

const { lang } = Astro.params;

// 2. Traducciones rápidas para la interfaz básica
const ui = {
    es: { title: "Sobre Mí", back: "Volver al inicio" },
    en: { title: "About Me", back: "Back to home" },
    ja: { title: "私について", back: "ホームに戻る" }
};

const t = ui[lang as keyof typeof ui] || ui.en;
---

<Layout title={t.title}>
    <section>
        <header>
            <h3>{t.title}</h3>
        </header>

        <div id="text">
            <p>I started to code when I was 10 years old.</p>
            <p>That was my first experience with computers.</p>
            <p>
                My first computer was an ASUS EEE PC 1015PX. Before that, a
                relative's computer was a Compaq Presario and, at the very
                beginning, their first computer was a second-hand Fujitsu
                Siemens SCENIC xB. But I was too young and I don't have clear
                memories, only that my relative told me I couldn’t go online
                because there was no cable—but really, they were just protecting
                me because they didn’t want me to surf the web (I was 5 or 6
                years old).
            </p>
            <p>
                Getting back to the Asus EEE PC—it still works, but barely. The
                charger broke, the battery had to be replaced, and even though
                it has an SSD now, I don’t use it anymore because the processor
                gets really hot, the keyboard has started to malfunction, and
                the screen is tiny. I have another desktop computer that’s much
                more powerful.
            </p>
            <p style="color:#ebcdf8">
                My version of the PC was special; it had 2GB of RAM instead of
                1GB!
            </p>
            <div class="containerpc">
                <div class="card-computer">
                    <img
                        src="/img/Fujitsu.jpg"
                        width="200px"
                        alt="Fujitsu Siemens xB"
                    />
                    <h4>Fujitsu Siemens SCENIC xB</h4>
                </div>
                <div class="card-computer">
                    <img
                        src="/img/compaq.jpg"
                        width="200px"
                        alt="Compaq Presario"
                    />
                    <h4>Compaq Presario</h4>
                </div>

                <div class="card-computer">
                    <img
                        src="/img/asus1015px.jpeg"
                        width="200px"
                        alt="Asus 1015PX"
                    />
                    <h4>Asus EEE PC 1015PX</h4>
                </div>
            </div>
            <header>
                <img
                    src="/img/cute_pc_girl.png"
                    class="no-radius"
                    alt="A cute anime girl with a computer and a programming book"
                />
                <h3>My current PC</h3>
            </header>
            <table>
                <tbody>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Component Name</th>
                        <th>Value</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>CPU</td>
                        <td>AMD Ryzen 7 5700X</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>GPU</td>
                        <td>Sapphire AMD RX 580 Special Edition</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>MotherBoard</td>
                        <td>Asus X370 Prime Pro</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>RAM</td>
                        <td>KFA DDR4-3600 16GB x2 8GB</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>OS</td>
                        <td>Linux Mint Cinnammon 22.2 / Windows 11 (Dual Boot)</td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>PC CASE</td>
                        <td>Phanteks Enthoo Pro.</td>
                    </tr>
                </tbody>
            </table>
            <div>
                <p>
                    My old first-generation <strong>Ryzen 1700 </strong>—one of the
                    first models released— retired not long ago (2026-06-06) (2017–2026) 
                </p>
                {/* Añadida la barra / inicial para que cargue desde public */}
                <img src="/img/cpu_changed_1700_5700x.webp" alt="A terminal showing CPU change">
            </div>
            <i>
                Sleep peacefully, my most beloved CPU, 1700 (🦋<i style="color:red">
                    Yes its an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Umineko_When_They_Cry" target="_blank">Umineko</a> ref
                </i>🦋)
            </i>
        </div>
    </section>
    {/* Enlace dinámico con el idioma actual */}
    <a href={`/${lang}/`} class="back-link">{t.back}</a>
</Layout>